abstract: After a year of negotiations with the contractor, the Pentagon said it would pay 4 percent less for each of the 32 radar-evading planes.
snippet: After a year of negotiations with the contractor, the Pentagon said it would pay 4 percent less for each of the 32 radar-evading planes.
lead_paragraph: Lockheed Martin expects to earn a profit in the high single digits under a new contract signed last week for the fifth batch of its radar-evading F-35 fighter planes, company officials said.

headline.main: Lockheed Profit on F-35 Jets Will Rise With New Contract
